  "prompt": "What is a normal waist size for a women?",
  "response": "A normal or healthy waist size for a woman can vary based on factors such as age, height, and overall body composition. However, the World Health Organization (WHO) provides general guidelines for waist circumference as an indicator of health risks associated with obesity.\n\nFor women, a waist circumference of:\n\n- Less than 80 cm (31.5 inches) is considered low risk.\n- 80 cm to 88 cm (31.5 to 34.6 inches) is considered moderate risk.\n- More than 88 cm (34.6 inches) is considered high risk.\n\nThese measurements are used to assess the risk of developing obesity-related health conditions such as heart disease, diabetes, and hypertension. It's important to consider these guidelines in conjunction with other health indicators, such as body mass index (BMI) and overall lifestyle.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about your waist size or overall health, it's best to consult with a healthcare professional who can provide personalized advice.",
